Internal Working

Internally, ArrayList is implemented as an array of Object References.  Basically, its an array of objects.

    Size vs Capacity :

    An array when created, its size has null elements but default capacity is generally 10.
    When this gets full, array resizes by copying elements to new array.

    When we add an element to ArrayList, it :
    - Checks Capacity
    - Resize if necessary ( usually larger is 1.5 times current capacity)
    - add the element  - copied into new array O(n)

    When removing elements, it:
    - Checks bounds (index in valid range)
    - Remove elements (once element is removed, all elements to right of removed element are shifted one position to left to fill gap.)
         [2,24,34,45,66]   Remove 34    [2, 24,45,66]
    - Reduce size : decremented by 1

    To reduce overhead, we can give capacity while declaring ArrayList.

    Time Complexity of ArrayList: O(n)

